ay be clash with obstacles. So the accuracy of the obstacle detection is very important for unmanned aerial vehicle movement. This paper proposes an obstacle detection system for unmanned aerial vehicle movement using correlation techniques of 3D Stereoscopic to examine the relationship of 3D images. The proposed system consists of two processes which are the obstacles detection in the movement vision, and objects avoidance by analysis of the correlation of 3D images. The correlation can analyze an obstacle of the movement. The system performances are evaluated by using 3D stereoscopic images input to the system to analyze it. The experiments results showed that accuracy of the detected obstacles in the movement vision is 83.33 %, and objects avoidance in the movement vision is 85.71 %.','Journal','Article','KKU Science Journal','[{\"$\": \"3D stereoscopic, Obstacle detection, Unmanned aerial vehicle\"}]','https://tci-thailand.org/wp-content/themes/magazine-style/tci_search/article.html?b3BlbkFydGljbGUmaWQ9MTQyMzg4',NULL,2014,'42','3',0,'681-692',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(566,'The Performance of Packet Scheduling with Fragmentation for CATV Networks','','Journal','Article','KKU Research Journal (Graduate Studies)','[{\"$\": \"\"}]','https://tci-thailand.org/wp-content/themes/magazine-style/tci_search/article.html?b3BlbkFydGljbGUmaWQ9NDcyNzQ',NULL,2005,'5','1',0,'70-77',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(567,'การแปลงภาพสามมิติแบบผูกพันกันด้วย OpenGL API','','Journal','Article','KKU Science Journal','[{\"$\": \"\"}]','https://tci-thailand.org/wp-content/themes/magazine-style/tci_search/article.html?b3BlbkFydGljbGUmaWQ9MzEwNDI',NULL,2004,'32','2',0,'71-79',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(568,'An Analysis and Classifi cation of Information for Tourism Development Planning at the Provincial Level','This research aims to analyze and classify the information essential for tourism development planning at the provincial level.  It is a part of the research on development of ontology of information for tourism development planning which will be on the next phase.  The research methods comprised of 3 steps: (1) Document analysis ? Documents related to tourism development planning and processes including the national and the provincial strategic plans for tourism, the standards for tourism promotion, the statistic reports on tourism in Thailand, and the travel & tourism competitiveness report, were analyzed in order to develop the information framework.  (2) User study ? A survey research was used by sending the questionnaires to collect data from the policy analysis and planning staffs of 77 Provincial Offices of Tourism and Sports in Thailand. And (3) Information classification ? The data from questionnaires were analyzed and classified using the classification approach, then checked by the researchers who specialized on tourism development and the policy analysis and planning staffs.  The research result provides a scope and structure of information for tourism development planning at provincial level which comprises of 2 domains: (1) Information for tourism planning development comprises of 3 classes, 11 concepts and 38 sub-concepts; and (2) Information for tourism planning processes comprises of 4 processes 16 tasks and 20 sub-tasks.','Journal','Article','Journal of Information Science','[{\"$\": \"\\u0e2a\\u0e32\\u0e23\\u0e2a\\u0e19\\u0e40\\u0e17\\u0e28\\u0e01\\u0e32\\u0e23\\u0e17\\u0e48\\u0e2d\\u0e07\\u0e40\\u0e17\\u0e35\\u0e48\\u0e22\\u0e27, \\u0e01\\u0e32\\u0e23\\u0e27\\u0e32\\u0e07\\u0e41\\u0e1c\\u0e19\\u0e01\\u0e32\\u0e23\\u0e17\\u0e48\\u0e2d\\u0e07\\u0e40\\u0e17\\u0e35\\u0e48\\u0e22\\u0e27, \\u0e01\\u0e32\\u0e23\\u0e08\\u0e31\\u0e14\\u0e2b\\u0e21\\u0e27\\u0e14\\u0e2b\\u0e21\\u0e39\\u0e48\\u0e2a\\u0e32\\u0e23\\u0e2a\\u0e19\\u0e40\\u0e17\\u0e28\"}]','https://tci-thailand.org/wp-content/themes/magazine-style/tci_search/article.html?b3BlbkFydGljbGUmaWQ9MTc3OTA4',NULL,2016,'34','2',0,'50-74',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(569,'LANDFORM CLASSIFICATION USING TOPOGRAPHIC POSITION INDEX IN NORTHEASTERN REGION OF THAILAND','This study is an attempt to classify the topographic position index (TPI) and landforms of the Northeastern, Thailand using GIS application to identify and extract geomorphologic properties of digital elevation model with 30 m. resolution. The landform classification is done using Andrew D. Weiss and Jeff Jenness algorithm, based on topographic position index. In this study used 6 grids cell size (3, 5, 9, 17, 25 and 33 grids) and the type of neighborhood was used square type. The landscape was classified into both slope position and landform category. Landform categories were determined by classifying the landscape using 2 TPI grids at different scales (such as neighborhood: a 25 grids and 33 grids). The Six slope position categories and 10 landform categories were generated. The result show that the small neighborhood can be classified micro structure better than macro structure such as small hills on plains, plains, etc. But the large neighborhood can be classified macro structure better than micro structure such as mountains, high ridge, valleys, etc.','Journal','Article','Journal of Remote Sensing and GIS Association of Thailand','[{\"$\": \"Topographic position index\"}, {\"$\": \"Landform classification\"}, {\"$\": \"Digital elevation model\"}, {\"$\": \"GIS\"}]','https://tci-thailand.org/wp-content/themes/magazine-style/tci_search/article.html?b3BlbkFydGljbGUmaWQ9NTkxNjI3',NULL,2019,'20','1-2',0,'1-8',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(570,'Using Standardized Vegetation Index to Assess Drought Areas in Northeast Thailand','','Journal','Article','Journal of Remote Sensing and GIS Association of Thailand','[{\"$\": \"NULL\"}]','https://tci-thailand.org/wp-content/themes/magazine-style/tci_search/article.html?b3BlbkFydGljbGUmaWQ9MTQ5NTIz',NULL,2014,'15','2',2,'25-38',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(571,'Relationship between Fingerprint Pattern and Multiple Intelligence','','Journal','Article','KKU Research Journal','[{\"$\": \"\"}]','https://tci-thailand.org/wp-content/themes/magazine-style/tci_search/article.html?b3BlbkFydGljbGUmaWQ9OTEwNjI',NULL,2011,'16','8',0,'951-964',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(572,'APPLICATION OF GEOINFORMATIONS TECHNOLOGY TO DETERMINING AREAS AT RISK OF ENCROACHMENT OF AGRICULTURE ON FOREST RESERVE IN PHU LUANG WILDLIFE SANCTUARY, LOEI PROVINCE','','Journal','Article','Journal of Remote Sensing and GIS Association of Thailand','[{\"$\": \"\"}]','https://tci-thailand.org/wp-content/themes/magazine-style/tci_search/article.html?b3BlbkFydGljbGUmaWQ9OTUwOTQ',NULL,2011,'12','1',1,'43-68',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(573,'Adapting Fleming-Type Learning Style Classifications to Deaf Student Behavior','This study presents the development of a novel integrated data fusion and assimilation technique to classify learning experiences and patterns among deaf students using Fleming’s model together with Thai Sign Language. Data were collected from students with hearing disabilities (Grades 7–9) studying at special schools in Khon Kaen and Udon Thani, Thailand. This research used six classification algorithms with data being resynthesized and improved via the application of feature selection, and the imbalanced data corrected using the synthetic minority oversampling technique. The collection of data from deaf students was evaluated using a 10-fold validation. This revealed that the multi-layer perceptron algorithm yields the highest accuracy. These research results are intended for application in further studies involving imbalanced data problems.','Journal','Article','Sustainability','[{\"$\":\"classification; deaf students; feature selection; imbalanced data; learning style\"}]','https://www.mdpi.com/2071-1050/14/8/4799','International Journal',2022,'14','8',0,'4799','10.3390/su14084799','This research was supported by the Research and Academic Affairs Promotion Fund, Faculty of Science, Khon Kaen University, fiscal year 2022 (RAAPF).',NULL,'2022-05-16 08:33:47','2022-05-16 11:59:27');
